{
  "texts": [
    "For example, a population of GW-driven circular SMBHBs produces a spectrum with α = -2/3 and amplitude A ≈ 10 -15, assuming f 0 = 1yr -1.",
    "h c (f) is connected to the differential energy content of the signal per logarithmic frequency through the equation:",
    "where H 0 is today's Hubble expansion parameter.",
    "We note that h c (f) and Ω(f) provide equivalent parametrizations of the spectrum.",
    "The former is more popular in the astrophysics domain, whereas the latter is the preferred choice for early Universe and cosmology."
  ]
}